Located at Dazu District in Chongqing, Dazu Rock Carvings was list as World Heritage Site by UNESCO in 1999.
Built between the late Tang Dynasty(618 ~907 D.C.) and early Song Dynasty (960 ~ 1279 D.C.), it's a religious cliff inscriptions. Most carvings took Buddhism culture as subject matter, and Confucianism and Taoism sculptures can also be seen in it.
